title: Exempts certain public employees and court clerks from provisions of law requiring the payment of an application fee for appointment as a notary public
summary: Exempts certain public employees who in the course of their duties and responsibilities provide notary service to the public without receiving remuneration and court clerks of the unified court system from provisions of law requiring the payment of an application fee for appointment as a notary public.
actClause: AN ACT to amend the executive law, in relation to exempting certain public employees and court clerks of the unified court system from provisions of law requiring the payment of an application fee for appointment as a notary public
